data.title: Kevin Federline

data.text: Actor Kevin Federline was renowned for his career in television which spans a decade. Federline began his acting career with roles in the series "CSI: Crime Scene Investigation" (2000-2015), "Nikki" (2000-02) and "One Tree Hill" (2003-2012). He also appeared in the TV special "InStyle Celebrity Weddings" (2004-05). A skilled dancer, he busted a move in "You Got Served" (2004) with Marques Houston. He made frequent appearances at awards shows, including "The 2006 MTV Video Music Awards" (2005-06) and "The 2006 Teen Choice Awards" (2005-06). Federline's distinctive voice can be heard on "Lil' Bush" (2006-08). Federline last acted in the Brendan Fletcher comedy "The Onion Movie" (2008). Previously married to Britney Spears, Federline had five children: Jayden James Federline, Jordan Kay Federline, Kaleb Federline, Kori Federline, and Sean Preston Federline.
